The paper deals with privacy-preserving communication and information disclosure, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The use of auxiliary knowledge by an adversary to infer sensitive information is a key concern in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CY). Finally, the application of the proposed framework to a health tele-monitoring scenario suggests a potential fit with the signal processing (cs.SI) community.
